					<head>Kabbalah</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85018546" rend="visible">
						<summary>A kabbalistic work of the school of Isaac Luria.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he"/>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="1r" to="271v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Sefer ha-kaṿanot</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">ספר הכונות</title>
							<author>
								<persName xml:lang="en" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/34704971">Vital, Ḥayyim ben Joseph, 1542-1620</persName>
								<persName xml:lang="he" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/34704971">ויטל, חיים בן יוסף</persName>
							</author>
							<note>
								<p>A recension of Menachem Azariah of Fano, with commentaries of Moshe Zacuto, Nathan Shapira, Benjamin Cohen, Benjamin ha-Levi, and others. Preceded by a number of additional paragraphs with references to the folios of the main work (folios 2r-7v).</p>
								<p>The comments are provided in the margin in various handwritings (folios 259r-261v contain additions of Joseph Irgas, in his owm handwriting). The title suggest that the manuscript was written by Menachem Azariah da Fano himself, but the handwriting seems to belong to Israel Yeshayah Norzi.</p>
								<p>See further <ref target="Avivi_2008" type="page">430-431</ref>.</p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Paper codex of the 17th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="chart">
								<support>Paper.</support>
								<extent>271 folios<dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
										<height>205</height>
										<width>150</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>145/155</height>
										<width>85/110</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>271 folios (+ 3 unfoliated paper flyleaves at the beginning and 3 at the end). </p>
									<p>Original Hebrew folation in the left upper corner of every recto, pages 1-232, not including the blank leaves from folio 16 to 253. Folios 2-7 have been separately folioed.</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>Quires of mostly 16 leaves each.</p>
								</collation>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1" ruledLines="28" writtenLines="28">
									<p>Uniform layout.</p>
									<p>Catchwords on every verso.</p>
									<p>Initial words in square characters.</p>
									<p>Folio 1 is a doodle page, in both Hebrew and Latin scripts.</p>
									<p>A provisional diagram (unfinished?), folio 269r.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="4">
							<summary>Italian cursive script of the 17th century.</summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="sole"/>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="owner">Yeshayah Yisrael Hezekiah Basan</name> and <name type="person" role="owner">Yosef Irgas</name>: inscribed in a note and a record of purchase, folio 1r. Folio 14r contains an ornamented owner's signature too.</p>
						</additions>
						<bindingDesc>
							<binding>
								<p>BM in-house.</p>
								<p>Spine: 'Menachem Azariah. Sepher Hak-Kavvanoth. Hebrew. Brit. Mus. Additional 27,143.'</p>
							</binding>
						</bindingDesc>
